964
01:01:41,364 --> 01:01:43,389
You know, trying this, trying that.

965
01:01:43,599 --> 01:01:46,534
And he said... Oh, he had an algorithm
he always wanted to use.

966
01:01:46,736 --> 01:01:49,534
That was...
It's not conceptually musical.

967
01:01:49,739 --> 01:01:52,367
It's more conceptual
at the algorithm level...

968
01:01:52,575 --> 01:01:55,544
...which was just filling sound buffer
with a square wave.

969
01:01:55,745 --> 01:02:00,409
And then just making passes through
averaging every adjacent sample...

970
01:02:00,616 --> 01:02:03,346
...till they got to be all the same.

971
01:02:03,553 --> 01:02:06,249
And that made
a chiming, bell-like sound.

972
01:02:08,725 --> 01:02:11,455
It was in the Mac, you know,
starting in 1984...

973
01:02:11,661 --> 01:02:13,458
...and it lasted up until the Mac II...

974
01:02:13,663 --> 01:02:18,100
